24 pull tabs, raffle board, punchboard, sports pool board, calcutta board, and series of
25 paddlewheel ticket cards sold or otherwise provided to a licensed organization or
26 organization that has a permit and shall purchase the stamps from the attorney
27 general for thirty-five cents each. Ten cents of each stamp sold by the attorney
28 general, up to thirty-six thousand dollars per biennium, must be credited to the
29 attorney general's operating fund to defray the costs of issuing and administering the
30 gaming stamps. If an organization hosts an event with a raffle board and only sells
